      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLUE ENERGY (1) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 19.62 beating Just Zorro. Has good speed and is aided by the cherry draw. Can make it back-to-back wins. ZING MATILDA (4) is rarely out of the finish, recording 31 places from 54 starts. Finished third (17.46) at Murray Bridge Straight last time making it three minors on end. Form here at the trip sound including six wins. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Leading chance. PLAY DIRTY (2) comes off an average effort last start when sixth at Rockhampton over 407m behind Regal Wolf (25.50) in a Grade 1/2. Placed at his previous run. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. In the mix. DEEP PURPLE (8) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.",
